docs.lead_paragraph: He broke into the entertainment business as a teenager, playing comedy clubs in Los Angeles and making his first appearance on “The Tonight Show” at age 18. He gained fame as a host of the 1980s NBC hit “Real People” before founding Entertainment Studios in 1993. That company has grown into an empire, with a film division and nearly two dozen television properties, including the Weather Channel, which it acquired last year for $300 million.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — For several months, some Uber passengers in Texas have been recorded on video as they have been driven to their destinations. docs.abstract: California’s largest utility needs to reach a settlement with victims of wildfires and other creditors while fending off calls for a state takeover.
docs.snippet: California’s largest utility needs to reach a settlement with victims of wildfires and other creditors while fending off calls for a state takeover.
docs.lead_paragraph: After an autumn marked by mass blackouts and wildfires, Pacific Gas & Electric is racing to craft a plan to escape bankruptcy. That plan needs to satisfy fire victims and state officials who are threatening to take over PG&E, California’s largest utility, unless executives improve its safety record.

headline.main: PG&E Struggles to Find a Way Out of Bankruptcy
